            <h1>Subway</h1>
                                    <div class="subway-wyoW9R_content">
            <table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>Bienvenue sur Subway.fr&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/subwayfrancais.jpg">&nbsp;<img class="size-full wp-image-263 alignright" title="subwayfrancais" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/subwayfrancais.jpg" alt="" width="37" height="20"></a></h1>
<p>Notre site vous propose des informations pratiques et gratuites pour vous guider dans vos d&eacute;placements lors de votre s&eacute;jour en France.</p>
<p>Vous y trouverez des plans de m&eacute;tro, tramway et bus des principales villes de France.</p>
<p>De lieux touristiques en restaurants gastronomiques, notre site a &eacute;t&eacute; con&ccedil;u pour aider les touristes am&eacute;ricains &agrave; se d&eacute;placer facilement et ais&eacute;ment dans les grandes villes de France. Si vous avez parfois eu des difficult&eacute;s &agrave; comprendre le syst&egrave;me de m&eacute;tro ou le r&eacute;seau de transport en France, c&rsquo;est fini !</p>
<p><br><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-subway.gif"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-257" title="image-subway" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-subway.gif" alt="" width="230" height="142"></a></p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>Welcome to Subway.fr&nbsp;<a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/subwayus.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-264 alignright" title="subwayus" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/subwayus.jpg" alt="" width="39" height="21"></a></h1>
<p>Our website will give you useful information for free in order to guide you through your trips during your journey in France.</p>
<p>You will find subway, tramway and bus maps for the main French cities.</p>
<p>From touristic places to famous restaurants, this website is meant to help American tourists to travel quickly around the major French cities. If you ever experienced difficulties understanding the subway and transport network in France, those days are over!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-258" title="image-subway" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-subway.jpg" alt="" width="230" height="142"></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>Le r&eacute;seau de tramway</strong></h1>
<p>Le r&eacute;seau de tramway&nbsp;est relativement nouveau &agrave; Paris. Il se compose de 4 lignes qui vous permettent de voyager en ext&eacute;rieur, au son de la cloche traditionnelle. Il est repr&eacute;sent&eacute; par le symbole T.&nbsp;La nuit de 0H30 &agrave; 5&nbsp;h&nbsp;30, vous pouvez emprunter les 42 lignes de bus de nuit qui traversent Paris, gr&acirc;ce au service &laquo;&nbsp;Noctilien&nbsp;&raquo;. Vous pouvez reconna&icirc;tre ses bus &agrave; la lettre N qu&rsquo;ils arborent avant le num&eacute;ro de ligne. Ils partent des 5 grandes stations (Gare de Lyon, Gare de l&rsquo;Est, Gare St-Lazare, Gare Montparnasse et Ch&acirc;telet) pour desservir 175 villes de banlieue.&nbsp;RER lines run from 4.45 a.m. to 1.30 a.m.Beware on the platform, there are short and very long trains</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>The Tramway network</strong></h1>
<p>The Tramway network&nbsp;is a relatively new network in Paris. There are only 4 tramway lines that let you discover the city in the outdoor, to the sound of its bell. It is represented by a T symbol.At night; from 0.30 a.m. to 5.30 a.m., you can always use the 42 dedicated night buses called &laquo;&nbsp;Noctilien&nbsp;&raquo; that run through Paris. You can recognize them to the N letter preceding the line number. They leave from the 5 main stations (Gare de Lyon, Gare de l&rsquo;Est, Gare St-Lazare, Gare Montparnasse and Ch&acirc;telet) and run through 175 suburban cities.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h2 lang="fr-FR">Le m&eacute;tro parisien</h2>
<p>Le m&eacute;tro parisien fonctionne de 5&nbsp;h&nbsp;30 &agrave; 1&nbsp;h du matin et vous emm&egrave;ne jusqu&rsquo;en proche banlieue.</p>
<p>Les entr&eacute;es du m&eacute;tro sont reconnaissables aux panneaux portant le logo M ou M&eacute;tro. Il existe pour cela 4 signal&eacute;tiques diff&eacute;rentes :</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h2>The Subway network in Paris</h2>
<p>The Paris subway network operates from 5.30a.m. to 1a.m. and extends to near suburbs.</p>
<p>Subway entrances are indicated by a Metro post. There are 4 different signs to symbolize it:</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1 lang="fr-FR"><strong>Le r&eacute;seau RER</strong></h1>
<p>Le r&eacute;seau RER relie la ville de Paris &agrave; la grande banlieue.</p>
<p>Il se compose en tout de 5 lignes diff&eacute;rentes indiqu&eacute;es par le panneau suivant&nbsp;:</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>The bus network</strong></h1>
<p>The bus network&nbsp;allows you to travel inside and outside Paris. Intra muros lines have a two-digit number whereas buses for the suburbs have a three-digit number.You need to hail the bus driver if you want him to stop at the bus station, otherwise, he will simply drive past you.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>Les lignes de RER</h1>
<p>Les lignes de RER fonctionnent de 4&nbsp;h 45 &agrave; 1&nbsp;h&nbsp;30 du matin. Soyez attentif sur le quai, car certains trains sont plus courts que d&rsquo;autres.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>The RER network</h1>
<p>The RER network&nbsp;links Paris to the far suburbs. There are 5 different lines shown by this post :</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h2 lang="fr-FR">Comment choisir et utiliser votre ticket de m&eacute;tro&nbsp;?</h2>
<h3 lang="fr-FR">LE TICKET T+, LE TICKET STANDARD POUR PARIS</h3>
<p>Il n&rsquo;est valable que sur un seul trajet. Vous pouvez l&rsquo;utiliser pour faire des correspondances dans le m&eacute;tro et le r&eacute;seau RER intra muros. En revanche, il ne vous permet pas de sortir de cette zone. Ce ticket vous permet &eacute;galement d&rsquo;emprunter les bus et de r&eacute;aliser une correspondance bus/bus ou bus/tram.</p>
<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-ticket.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-240" title="image-ticket" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-ticket.jpg" alt="" width="230" height="153"></a></p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h2>How to choose and use your subway ticket?</h2>
<h3>THE T+ TICKET, THE ORDINARY SUBWAY TICKET FOR PARIS</h3>
<p>It is valid for one trip. You are allowed to connect throughout the subway and Paris RER network. You can&rsquo;t leave Paris though. You can also travel by buses with this ticket and make bus/bus or bus/tram connections.</p>
<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-ticket1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-253" title="image-ticket" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-ticket1.jpg" alt="" width="230" height="153"></a></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>Bon plan&nbsp;:</strong>&nbsp;le ticket T+ est moins cher si vous l&rsquo;achetez par 10. Il vous faut alors demander un &laquo;&nbsp;carnet&nbsp;&raquo;.</h1>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>Tip:</strong>&nbsp;The T+ ticket is cheaper if you buy 10 at a time. In this case you need to ask for a &laquo;&nbsp;carnet&nbsp;&raquo;.</h1>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>Attention !&nbsp;</strong>Les chauffeurs de bus vendent des tickets en voiture qui ne vous permettent pas de continuer votre trajet sur le r&eacute;seau. C&rsquo;est d&rsquo;ailleurs ce qu&rsquo;indique la mention &laquo;&nbsp;SANS CORRESPONDANCES&nbsp;&raquo;.</h1>
<p>Le r&eacute;seau de m&eacute;tro et autres transports publics se divise en 6 zones.</p>
<p lang="fr-FR">Plus vous choisissez un chiffre &eacute;lev&eacute; et plus vous &ecirc;tes loin de Paris.</p>
<p lang="fr-FR"><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-rer.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-246" title="image-rer" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-rer.jpg" alt="" width="223" height="150"></a></p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1><strong>Be careful!</strong>&nbsp;The bus drivers sell different tickets that do not allow any connection. Those tickets say &laquo;&nbsp;SANS CORRESPONDANCES&nbsp;&raquo;</h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The subway and public transport network is divided into 6 zones.</p>
<p>The higher number you choose, the farther you&rsquo;ll be able to travel.</p>
<p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-rer1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-247" title="image-rer" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20240301014446im_/http://www.subway.fr/files/2012/02/image-rer1.jpg" alt="" width="223" height="150"></a></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>Pour les zones de banlieue</h1>
<p lang="fr-FR">Si vous voulez vous rendre hors de Paris, il vous faut un ticket sp&eacute;cial valable pour plusieurs zones.</p>
<p lang="fr-FR">Par exemple, le Ch&acirc;teau de Versailles se trouve en zone 4, l&rsquo;a&eacute;roport Charles de Gaulle en zone 5, l&rsquo;a&eacute;roport d&rsquo;Orly en zone 4 et Disneyland Paris en zone 5.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>For suburban areas</h1>
<p>If you want to travel to a place outside Paris, you&rsquo;ll need to buy a special ticket with several zones.</p>
<p>For example, Ch&acirc;teau de Versailles is in zone 4, Charles de Gaulle airport is in zone 5, Orly airport is in zone 4 and Disneyland Resort Paris is in zone 5.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>Conseils aux voyageurs</h1>
<p>COMMENT ALLER &Agrave; L&rsquo;A&Eacute;ROPORT EN M&Eacute;TRO&nbsp;?</p>
<p lang="fr-FR">Pour vous rendre dans un a&eacute;roport en transports en commun, vous aurez besoin d&rsquo;un ticket sp&eacute;cial.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>Travelling tips</h1>
<p>HOW TO GO TO THE AIRPORTS BY USING THE SUBWAY?</p>
<p>You&rsquo;ll need a special ticket to travel from and to the airports.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>MOBILIS, LE PASSEPORT POUR LA JOURN&Eacute;E</h1>
<p>Le ticket Mobilis vous permet de choisir un certain nombre de zones. Il est valable pendant toute la journ&eacute;e o&ugrave; vous le compostez. Par exemple, si vous le validez &agrave; midi, il sera valable jusqu&rsquo;&agrave; 1H30 du matin.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>MOBILIS, THE ONE-DAY TICKET</h1>
<p>Mobilis lets you choose the number of selected zones. This ticket is valid during the whole day you first stamp it. For example, if you stamp your Mobilis ticket at noon, it will be valid until 1.30 a.m. for the subway.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>La gr&egrave;ve</h1>
<h3 lang="fr-FR">Les gr&egrave;ves ne devraient plus &ecirc;tre un cauchemar pour les touristes en France.</h3>
<p>En effet, gr&acirc;ce &agrave; une nouvelle loi de 2007, m&ecirc;me en cas de gr&egrave;ve, les services publics tels que les transports en commun doivent fournir un service minimum pour emp&ecirc;cher tout blocage du pays.</p>
<p>Faites attention aux pickpockets&nbsp;!<br>Il est interdit de fumer dans le m&eacute;tro.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>Strike</h1>
<h3>Strikes should no longer be a problem for tourists.</h3>
<p>A new law passed in 2007 guarantees a minimum public transport service even in case of strike, so the subway network should never be at a complete standstill.</p>
<p>Beware of pickpockets<br>The Subway is a non-smoking area.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table border="0" width="950" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="465"><col width="10"><col width="465"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr valign="TOP">
<td width="465">
<h1>PARIS VISITE, LE TICKET MALIN POUR LES TOURISTES</h1>
<p lang="fr-FR">Si vous avez l&rsquo;intention de visiter certains monuments, pensez &agrave; la carte &laquo;&nbsp;Paris Visite&nbsp;&raquo;.</p>
<p>Ce ticket a l&rsquo;avantage de vous permettre de choisir un nombre de zones et une dur&eacute;e&nbsp;: 1, 2, 3 ou 5 jours. Ce ticket de transport malin vous offre en plus des r&eacute;ductions pour l&rsquo;entr&eacute;e de certains monuments.</p>
</td>
<td width="10">&nbsp;</td>
<td width="465">
<h1>PARIS VISITE, THE TOURISTIC TICKET</h1>
<p>If you plan on visiting sites or monuments, it might be a good idea to choose a &laquo;&nbsp;Paris Visite&nbsp;&raquo; card.</p>
<p>You can select the number of zones you need and also the number of days: 1, 2, 3 or 5 days. This travel ticket will also offer you discounts in some touristic sites.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
